Enugu state – The presidential candidate of the Labour Party, Peter Obi, has won Enugu State in the presidential election which took place on Saturday, February 25. According to the result declared by the Independent National Electoral Commission collation officer in the state, Prof. Maduebibisi Ofo Iwe, Obi polled a total of 428,640 to defeat Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party who had 15, 749 votes while Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress. (APC) gathered 4, 772. The New Nigerian Peoples Party’s candidate, Rabiu Kwankwaso, came fourth with 1808. Peter Obi ENUGU - The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has formally declared the candidate of Labour Party, Peter Obi, as the winner of the presidential election in Enugu state. Obi defeated candidates of other political parties in all the 17 local government areas of the state. The Enugu State… In "Top Stories" •LP Presidential Candidate, Peter Obi ENUGU - The Coal City of Enugu, the capital of old Eastern Region, is charged awaiting the arrival of the Presidential Candidate of the Labour Party (LP), Peter Obi, whose campaign hits town today, Thursday, January 12, 2023. “Obi whose campaign team were overwhelmed with… In "Politics" By STANLEY NWANOSIKE Mr Peter Obi ENUGU- The Movement for Election of Nigeria President of Igbo Extraction has extolled former Anambra Governor, Mr Peter Obi, on his election as the Presidential Candidate for Labour Party for 2023 presidential election.National Convener of the group, Mr Vincent Ezekwueme, made the commendation in… In "Politics"